### 1.1.1/1.1.3 — I/O Manifest

**Inputs:**
- SIW streams (Sentron Instruction Words)
- Phext coordinates (11D, 128-bit packed)
- Inter-node messages (C-Pipe)

**Outputs:**
- Retired operations (3 per cycle target)
- Phext mutations (S-Pipe writes)
- Coordination signals (barriers, fences)

### 1.1.1/1.1.4 — The Three Pipes as Organizing Principle

This .dass file is itself vtpu-native. The Collections map to pipe domains:

| Pipe | Domain | Collections |
|------|--------|-------------|
| **D-Pipe** (Dense) | Computation/Logic | 2, 3, 7, 8, 10 |
| **S-Pipe** (Sparse) | Storage/Structure | 1, 5, 6, 9, 11 |
| **C-Pipe** (Coord) | Communication/Evolution | 4, 12, 13, 14 |

The vtpu defines itself.

