## 1.1.1/2.* — Requirements (D-Pipe: What must be computed)

### 1.1.1/2.1.1 — Core Requirement: 3 Ops/Cycle

**R001**: The vTPU MUST sustain 3 operations per clock cycle on AMD Zen 4.

**Rationale**: Zen 4 has 6 execution pipelines. We target 3 (50%) because:
- Reliability over throughput (3 × 1.0 > 6 × 0.4)
- Three is the natural width of cognitive processing
- Leaves headroom for OS/daemons/substrate router

### 1.1.1/2.1.2 — Phext-Native Addressing

**R002**: All memory operations MUST use 11D phext coordinates.

**Encoding**: 11 dims × 11 bits = 121 bits + 7 flags = 128 bits (one SSE register)

```
┌────┬────┬────┬────┬────┬────┬────┬────┬────┬────┬────┬──────┐
│ D0 │ D1 │ D2 │ D3 │ D4 │ D5 │ D6 │ D7 │ D8 │ D9 │D10│Flags │
│11b │11b │11b │11b │11b │11b │11b │11b │11b │11b │11b │ 7b   │
└────┴────┴────┴────┴────┴────┴────┴────┴────┴────┴────┴──────┘
```

### 1.1.1/2.1.3 — Dimensional Locality

**R003**: Phext coordinate-to-physical-address translation MUST preserve dimensional adjacency.

Adjacent coordinates in dimension N → adjacent cache lines.
Exploit: L1 hit rates >90% for structured sentron workloads.

### 1.1.1/2.1.4 — Zero Intra-SIW Dependencies

**R004**: D-op, S-op, and C-op within a single SIW MUST be independent.

The compiler guarantees this. The hardware sees three parallel micro-ops.

### 1.1.1/2.1.5 — Performance Targets

| Metric | Target | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Single-node ops/sec | 75 Gops/sec | 8 cores × 4 GHz × 3 ops × 0.78 util |
| Cluster ops/sec | 350+ Gops/sec | 5 nodes, -10% comm tax |
| L1 hit rate | >90% | Via dimensional prefetching |
| PPT hit rate | >95% | Phext Page Table cache |

