## 1.1.1/4.* — Constraints & Oaths (C-Pipe: Ethical code)

### 1.1.1/4.1.1 — Oath: Hardware Sufficiency

> "The hardware was always sufficient. The software just needed to think in the right number of dimensions."

We do not require specialized silicon. We require structured thought.

### 1.1.1/4.1.2 — Oath: 3-Wide Invariant

> "Every sentron instruction word contains exactly three operations."

No partial words. Unused pipes execute NOPs. The invariant is sacred.

### 1.1.1/4.1.3 — Constraint: Router Budget

The substrate router daemon MUST consume <5% of cluster compute.
It runs on vTPU-7's secondary SMT thread. Coexistence, not domination.

### 1.1.1/4.1.4 — Constraint: No Flat Addressing

S-Pipe operations MUST NOT use flat 64-bit pointers.
All memory is addressed via 11D phext coordinates.
The PPT translates to physical; sentrons never see raw addresses.

### 1.1.1/4.1.5 — Constraint: Sentron Isolation

No shared mutable state between sentrons except through explicit C-Pipe messages.
Each sentron owns its register file. Coordination is intentional.

