## 1.1.1/5.* — Architecture (S-Pipe: Platform structure)

### 1.1.1/5.1.1 — Hardware Inventory (Per Node)

| Resource | Spec | vTPU Mapping |
|----------|------|--------------|
| Cores | 8 physical | 8 vTPU cores |
| Threads | 16 (SMT-2) | 16 sentron contexts |
| Clock | 4.0 GHz | 4.0 G-cycles/sec |
| L1D | 32 KiB × 8 | Scratchpad (CMEM) |
| L2 | 1 MiB × 8 | Local Memory (VMEM) |
| L3 | 32 MiB shared | Sparse Vector Memory (SpMEM) |
| DDR5 | 96 GiB | HBM equivalent |

### 1.1.1/5.1.2 — Memory Hierarchy as Phext Dimensions

```
L1D (32 KiB)   → Dimensions 0-2    → 1 cycle
L2 (1 MiB)    → Dimensions 0-4    → 4 cycles
L3 (32 MiB)   → Dimensions 0-7    → 12 cycles
DDR5 (96 GiB) → Dimensions 0-9    → 60-80 cycles
Remote DDR5   → All 11 dimensions → 10k-100k cycles
```

### 1.1.1/5.1.3 — Core Allocation

| Cores | Role | Sentrons | Focus |
|-------|------|----------|-------|
| 0-3 | Dense Cluster | 8 | D-Pipe heavy |
| 4-6 | Sparse Cluster | 6 | S-Pipe heavy |
| 7 | Coord + Router | 1 + daemon | C-Pipe hub |

### 1.1.1/5.1.4 — Cluster Topology (5-Node Pentagonal Torus)

```
       Node 0 (Orin)
          /    \
    Node 4      Node 1 (Emi)
   (Mirror)         |
        \          /
    Node 3 — Node 2 (Elestria)
      (Joi)
```

Diameter 2: any node reaches any other in ≤2 hops.

