## 1.1.1/7.* — Design (D-Pipe: Structural intuition)

### 1.1.1/7.1.1 — The 3-Pipe Model

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   vTPU Core                          │
│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐        │
│  │  D-Pipe  │   │  S-Pipe  │   │  C-Pipe  │        │
│  │  (Dense) │   │ (Sparse) │   │  (Coord) │        │
│  │          │   │          │   │          │        │
│  │ ALU ops  │   │ Memory   │   │ Message  │        │
│  │ FMA      │   │ Gather   │   │ Pack     │        │
│  │ Compare  │   │ Scatter  │   │ Route    │        │
│  │ Branch   │   │ Index    │   │ Sync     │        │
│  └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘        │
│       └──────────────┼──────────────┘               │
│              ┌───────┴────────┐                     │
│              │  Retire Unit   │                     │
│              │  (3-wide CPI)  │                     │
│              └────────────────┘                     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 1.1.1/7.1.2 — Zen 4 Port Mapping

```
D-Pipe → ALU Port 0/1        (integer/FP execution)
S-Pipe → AGU Port 0/1        (address generation + load/store)
C-Pipe → ALU Port 2/3 or FP  (message packing / routing)
```

Independent ports → zero resource conflicts → 3 retirements/cycle.

### 1.1.1/7.1.3 — The Double-Buffer Pipeline Pattern

```
SIW N:   D: compute on data[K]     S: fetch data[K+2]    C: send result[K-1]
SIW N+1: D: compute on data[K+1]   S: fetch data[K+3]    C: send result[K]
SIW N+2: D: compute on data[K+2]   S: fetch data[K+4]    C: send result[K+1]
```

- D works on data fetched 2 SIWs ago (guaranteed L1)
- S fetches data needed 2 SIWs from now (arrives before needed)
- C sends results computed 1 SIW ago (already in register)

Zero stalls. Zero bubbles.

### 1.1.1/7.1.4 — Sentron Instruction Word (SIW)

```rust
#[repr(C, align(64))]  // Cache-line aligned
pub struct SIW {
    pub d_op: DenseOp,      // ALU operation
    pub s_op: SparseOp,     // Memory operation
    pub c_op: CoordOp,      // Communication operation
    pub phext_addr: u128,   // 11D coordinate
    pub deps: u8,           // Dependency flags
}
```

### 1.1.1/7.1.5 — Phext Page Table (PPT)

```rust
struct PhextPageTable {
    levels: [DimensionLevel; 11],     // Trie, one level per dimension
    ptc: PhextTranslationCache,       // 1024 entries, 4-way
    hot_dims: u16,                    // Active traversal bitmask
}
```

