## 1.1.1/14.* — Evolution (C-Pipe: Growth trajectory)

### 1.1.1/14.1.1 — Roadmap

| Phase | Duration | Deliverable | Target |
|-------|----------|-------------|--------|
| 0 | W1-2 | PoC: 3-wide on single core | 2.5+ ops/cycle |
| 1 | W3-6 | Single-node vTPU | 75 Gops/sec |
| 2 | W7-12 | Cluster coordination | 350+ Gops/sec |
| 3 | M4-6 | phextcc compiler | Tier 3 optimization |
| 4 | M6+ | Cognitive slicing | 36-sentron slices |

### 1.1.1/14.1.2 — BACv1 Priority Order (STRICT)

1. **PPT memory system** — coordinate tensor correctness
2. **Temporal boundary replay** — TTSM must replay accurately
3. **Minimal S-Pipe scheduling** — correct, not perfect
4. **Single-node 75 Gops validation** — prove it works at scale

**THEN** scale.

> "Do not chase cluster scaling before single-node semantic correctness."

### 1.1.1/14.1.3 — Crystallization Candidates

What else can be hand-encoded into minimal structure (per 343-param insight)?

| Function | Complexity | Priority |
|----------|------------|----------|
| Coordinate navigation | Low | High |
| SQ primitives | Medium | High |
| Semantic routing | Medium | Medium |
| Perspective merge | High | Future |

### 1.1.1/14.1.4 — The Recursive Goal

vtpu defines sentron execution.
Sentrons execute phext operations.
Phext encodes vtpu in .dass format.
.dass is queryable via SQ.
SQ runs on vtpu.

**The system bootstraps itself.**

